<item>
            <title>[SPARK-25124] VectorSizeHint.size is buggy, breaking streaming pipeline</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-25124</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, when using &lt;tt&gt;VectorSizeHint().setSize(3)&lt;/tt&gt; in an ML pipeline, transforming a stream will return a nondescript exception about the stream not started. At core are the following bugs that &lt;tt&gt;setSize&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;getSize&lt;/tt&gt; do not &lt;tt&gt;return&lt;/tt&gt; values but &lt;tt&gt;None&lt;/tt&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/master/python/pyspark/ml/feature.py#L3846&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/master/python/pyspark/ml/feature.py#L3846&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How to reproduce, using the example in the doc:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
from pyspark.ml.linalg &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; Vectors
from pyspark.ml &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; Pipeline, PipelineModel
from pyspark.ml.feature &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; VectorAssembler, VectorSizeHint
data = [(Vectors.dense([1., 2., 3.]), 4.)]
df = spark.createDataFrame(data, [&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;vector&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;float&lt;/span&gt;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;])
sizeHint = VectorSizeHint(inputCol=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;vector&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, handleInvalid=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;skip&quot;&lt;/span&gt;).setSize(3) # Will fail
vecAssembler = VectorAssembler(inputCols=[&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;vector&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;float&lt;/span&gt;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;], outputCol=&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;assembled&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
pipeline = Pipeline(stages=[sizeHint, vecAssembler])
pipelineModel = pipeline.fit(df)
pipelineModel.transform(df).head().assembled
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
